{%- comment -%}
  Collection card (spec §5.2, §6). Two presentations of the same data —
  `mode` is a per-instance param, not a global setting, since the sections
  that will call this (featured collections, collection lists — later
  milestones) each decide their own default rather than sharing one site-wide
  choice; that's a real difference from product-card, which spec treats as
  identical everywhere it appears.

  Accepts:
  - collection (required)
  - mode: 'standard' (default, image + title/count below) | 'overlay' (scrim +
    centered title on the image)
  - aspect_ratio: default '1/1' (spec: "image (3:4 or square)")
  - show_description: bool, default false
  - priority: passed through to the image
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign card_mode = mode | default: 'standard'
  assign ratio = aspect_ratio | default: '1/1'
-%}
<a href="{{ collection.url }}" class="collection-card collection-card--{{ card_mode }}">
  <div class="collection-card__media aspect-ratio" style="aspect-ratio: {{ ratio }};">
    {% render 'responsive-image', image: collection.featured_image, sizes: '(min-width: 990px) 33vw, 50vw', wrap: false, class: 'collection-card__image', priority: priority %}

    {%- if card_mode == 'overlay' -%}
      <span class="collection-card__scrim" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      {%- comment -%} Reuses Scheme 2's token set purely for guaranteed text
      contrast against arbitrary photography — same technique as the
      transparent header (Milestone 3), not a statement about dark mode. {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="collection-card__overlay-content color-scheme-scheme-2">
        <h3 class="collection-card__title">{{ collection.title }}</h3>
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>

  {%- if card_mode == 'standard' -%}
    <div class="collection-card__info">
      <h3 class="collection-card__title">{{ collection.title }}</h3>
      <span class="collection-card__count text-small">{{ collection.products_count }} {{ 'collections.product_count' | t }}</span>
      {%- if show_description and collection.description != blank -%}
        <p class="collection-card__description text-small">{{ collection.description | strip_html | truncate: 100 }}</p>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>
  {%- endif -%}
</a>
